[b]Tutorial on:[/b] Adding skillcape trimming.
[b]Class modified:[/b] Client.java
[b]Difficulty:[/b] 3 of 10.
____________________________________

[b]Step 1![/b]
Under the [code=java]public class client extends Player implements Runnable {[/code] add this integer array:

[code=java]	public int Skillcape[] = { // Contains all untrimmed skillcape id's.
		2677, 2683, 2680, 2701, 2686, 2689, 2692, 
		2731, 2734, 2716, 2728, 2695, 2713, 2725, 
		2722, 2707, 2704, 2710, 2719, 2737, 2698
	};

	public int SkillcapeT[] = { // Contains all trimmed skillcape id's.
		4319, 4329, 4359, 4341, 4351, 4347, 4343,
		4325, 4353, 4337, 4335, 4321, 4327, 4357,
		4345, 4339, 4317, 4361, 4355, 4331, 4333
	};[/code][b][/b]

[b]Step 2![/b]
Under that add this method:

[code=java]	private void SkillcapeTrim() {
		/** 
		 * This will check if trimming is required!
		 */
		for (int i = 0; i < 20; i++) {
			if ((playerEquipment[playerCape] == Skillcape[i]) && (MaxedSkills() >= 2)) {
				playerEquipment[playerCape] = SkillcapeT[i];
				playerEquipmentN[playerCape] = 1;
				setEquipment(SkillcapeT[i], 1, playerCape);
				updateRequired = true;
				appearanceUpdateRequired = true;
			}
		}
		/** 
		 * This will check if untrimming is required.
		 */
		for (int i = 0; i < 20; i++) {
			if ((playerEquipment[playerCape] == SkillcapeT[i]) && (MaxedSkills() < 2)) {
				playerEquipment[playerCape] = Skillcape[i];
				playerEquipmentN[playerCape] = 1;
				setEquipment(Skillcape[i], 1, playerCape);
				updateRequired = true;
				appearanceUpdateRequired = true;
			}
		}
	}[/code]

[b]Step 3![/b]
You'll also need this:

[code=java]        public int MaxedSkills() {
                int maxedSklls = 0;
                for (int level : playerLevel) {
                        if (level >= 99) {
                                maxedSklls++;
                        }
                }
                return maxedSklls;
        }[/code]

[b]Step 4![/b]
Under [code=java]public boolean process() {[/code] add:
[code=java]	for (int i = 0; i < Skillcape.length; i++) {
		if (playerEquipment[playerCape] == Skillcape[i] || playerEquipment[playerCape] == SkillcapeT[i]) {
			SkillcapeTrim();
		}
	}[/code]

[b]Step 5![/b]
Also add the [code=java]	for (int i = 0; i < Skillcape.length; i++) {
		if (playerEquipment[playerCape] == Skillcape[i] || playerEquipment[playerCape] == SkillcapeT[i]) {
			SkillcapeTrim();
		}
	}[/code] below [code=java]if (oldLevel < getLevelForXP(playerXP[skill])) {[/code]

